{"kind":"article","identifier":{"interfaceLanguage":"swift","url":"doc:\/\/TUIkit\/documentation\/TUIkit\/FocusSystem"},"sections":[],"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/TUIkit\/documentation\/TUIkit"]]},"seeAlsoSections":[{"generated":true,"anchor":"Guides","title":"Guides","identifiers":["doc:\/\/TUIkit\/documentation\/TUIkit\/StateManagement","doc:\/\/TUIkit\/documentation\/TUIkit\/ThemingGuide","doc:\/\/TUIkit\/documentation\/TUIkit\/StatusBarGuide","doc:\/\/TUIkit\/documentation\/TUIkit\/AppearanceAndColors","doc:\/\/TUIkit\/documentation\/TUIkit\/Preferences","doc:\/\/TUIkit\/documentation\/TUIkit\/CustomViews","doc:\/\/TUIkit\/documentation\/TUIkit\/KeyboardShortcuts","doc:\/\/TUIkit\/documentation\/TUIkit\/PaletteReference","doc:\/\/TUIkit\/documentation\/TUIkit\/ListAndTable","doc:\/\/TUIkit\/documentation\/TUIkit\/LayoutSystem"]}],"primaryContentSections":[{"content":[{"anchor":"Overview","text":"Overview","type":"heading","level":2},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"TUIkit provides a focus system that lets users move between interactive views (buttons, menus, text fields) using Tab, Shift+Tab, or arrow keys. The system consists of three parts:","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"items":[{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"FocusManager"}]},{"type":"text","text":": Tracks which element is focused, handles navigation"}]}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"identifier":"doc:\/\/TUIkit\/documentation\/TUIkit\/Focusable","isActive":true,"type":"reference"}]},{"text":": Protocol that views adopt to receive focus","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"inlineContent":[{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/TUIkit\/documentation\/TUIkit\/FocusState"}],"type":"strong"},{"text":": Lightweight state object that views use to query and request focus","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]}],"type":"unorderedList"},{"anchor":"How-Focus-Works","text":"How Focus Works","type":"heading","level":2},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Every frame, the "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"FocusManager"},{"type":"text","text":" is cleared and interactive views re-register themselves during rendering. This means focus registrations are always in sync with the current view tree: removed views are automatically unregistered."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The focus order follows the rendering order: the first focusable view rendered is first in the Tab cycle."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"anchor":"The-Focusable-Protocol","text":"The Focusable Protocol","type":"heading","level":2},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Views that want to receive focus conform to ","type":"text"},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/TUIkit\/documentation\/TUIkit\/Focusable"},{"text":":","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"code":["public protocol Focusable: AnyObject {","    var focusID: String { get }","    var canBeFocused: Bool { get }","    func onFocusReceived()","    func onFocusLost()","    func handleKeyEvent(_ event: KeyEvent) -> Bool","}"],"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift"},{"items":[{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"focusID"}],"type":"strong"},{"text":": Unique identifier for this focusable element","type":"text"}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"code":"canBeFocused","type":"codeVoice"}]},{"type":"text","text":": Whether focus can move to this element (default: "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"true"},{"type":"text","text":")"}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"onFocusReceived()"}]},{"text":": Called when this element gains focus (default: no-op)","type":"text"}]}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"code":"onFocusLost()","type":"codeVoice"}]},{"type":"text","text":": Called when this element loses focus (default: no-op)"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"code":"handleKeyEvent(_:)","type":"codeVoice"}]},{"type":"text","text":": Handle a key event while focused; return "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"true"},{"type":"text","text":" if consumed"}]}]}],"type":"unorderedList"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"A default extension provides sensible defaults for "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"canBeFocused"},{"type":"text","text":" ("},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"true"},{"type":"text","text":"), "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"onFocusReceived()"},{"type":"text","text":", and "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"onFocusLost()"},{"type":"text","text":" (both no-ops). Only "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"focusID"},{"type":"text","text":" and "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"handleKeyEvent(_:)"},{"type":"text","text":" must be implemented."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"anchor":"Using-FocusState","text":"Using FocusState","type":"heading","level":2},{"inlineContent":[{"identifier":"doc:\/\/TUIkit\/documentation\/TUIkit\/FocusState","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"text":" is the user-facing API for checking and requesting focus inside a view:","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"code":["let focusState = FocusState(id: \"my-button\", focusManager: context.environment.focusManager)","","\/\/ Check if this element is currently focused","if focusState.isFocused {","    \/\/ render with focus indicator","}","","\/\/ Programmatically request focus","focusState.requestFocus()"],"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Built-in views like ","type":"text"},{"isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/TUIkit\/documentation\/TUIkit\/Button","type":"reference"},{"text":" and ","type":"text"},{"isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/TUIkit\/documentation\/TUIkit\/Menu","type":"reference"},{"text":" create their own ","type":"text"},{"code":"FocusState","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" internally: you only need it when building custom focusable views.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"anchor":"Navigation-Keys","text":"Navigation Keys","type":"heading","level":2},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"The ","type":"text"},{"code":"FocusManager","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" responds to these keys during dispatch:","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"table","rows":[[[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Key"}]}],[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Action"}]}]],[[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Tab"}]}],[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Move focus to the next element","type":"text"}]}]],[[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Shift+Tab","type":"text"}]}],[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Move focus to the previous element","type":"text"}]}]],[[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Arrow Down \/ Right"}]}],[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Move focus to the next element"}]}]],[[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Arrow Up \/ Left"}]}],[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Move focus to the previous element"}]}]]],"header":"row"},{"anchor":"FocusRegistration-Helper","text":"FocusRegistration Helper","type":"heading","level":2},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Built-in interactive views use the internal ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"FocusRegistration"},{"text":" helper to avoid boilerplate. It handles three tasks in one call:","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"items":[{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Persist a focus ID"}],"type":"strong"},{"text":" via ","type":"text"},{"code":"StateStorage","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" so it remains stable across renders","type":"text"}]}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"strong","inlineContent":